library(ggplot2)
library(gmodels)
# 1. Gender and Stream relationship
# Create contingency table
data = read.csv("C:\\Users\\ALOK\\Desktop\\project\\cleaneddata.csv")
gender_stream_table <- table(data$Gender, data$Stream)

# Chi-square test
chisq.test(gender_stream_table)
## 
##  Pearson's Chi-squared test with Yates' continuity correction
## 
## data:  gender_stream_table
## X-squared = 7.527, df = 1, p-value = 0.006078
# Visualization
ggplot(data, aes(x = Stream, fill = Gender)) +
  geom_bar(position = "dodge") +
  labs(title = "Gender Distribution Across Streams",
       x = "Stream", y = "Count") +
  theme_minimal()

ggplot(data, aes(x = Stream, fill = Gender)) +
  geom_bar(position = "fill") +
  labs(title = "Gender Proportions Across Streams",
       x = "Stream", y = "Proportion") +
  theme_minimal()

Stream and reasons

# First, we need to split the Reasons column which contains multiple values
library(tidyr)
library(stringr) # split column which contains multiple values

# Split reasons into separate rows
reasons_split <- data %>%
  separate_rows(Reasons, sep = ", ")

# Create contingency table
stream_reasons_table <- table(reasons_split$Stream, reasons_split$Reasons)

# Chi-square test
chisq.test(stream_reasons_table)
## 
##  Pearson's Chi-squared test
## 
## data:  stream_reasons_table
## X-squared = 16.924, df = 4, p-value = 0.002
# Visualize
ggplot(reasons_split, aes(x = Reasons, fill = Stream)) +
  geom_bar(position = "dodge") +
  labs(title = "Reasons for Choosing Field by Stream",
       x = "Reason", y = "Count") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

prop.table(table(data$Gender, data$Stream), margin = 1) # Row proportions
##         
##           Non-STEM      STEM
##   Female 0.8120301 0.1879699
##   Male   0.6569343 0.3430657
prop.test(table(data$Gender, data$Stream)) # Test for equal proportions
## 
##  2-sample test for equality of proportions with continuity correction
## 
## data:  table(data$Gender, data$Stream)
## X-squared = 7.527, df = 1, p-value = 0.006078
## alternative hypothesis: two.sided
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  0.04411053 0.26608100
## sample estimates:
##    prop 1    prop 2 
## 0.8120301 0.6569343

data$Performance_ordinal <- factor(data$Performance, ordered = TRUE)
model <- polr(Performance_ordinal ~ Stream, data = data, Hess = TRUE)
summary(model)

#install.packages("ggraph")
library(ggraph)
## Warning: package 'ggraph' was built under R version 4.4.3
career_edges <- data %>% separate_rows(CareerGoals, sep = ", ") %>%
  count(Stream, CareerGoals)
ggraph(career_edges, layout = "fr") +
  geom_edge_link(aes(width = n)) +
  geom_node_point() +
  geom_node_text(aes(label = name), repel = TRUE)
